President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Adam H. Sterling is nominated for Ambassador to the Slovak Republic, Department of State. Morton H. Halperin is nominated for Member, Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Dr. Dain Borges is nominated for Member, National Council on the Humanities. Dr. Thavolia Glymph is nominated for Member, National Council on the Humanities. Dr. Deborah Wong is nominated for Member, National Council on the Humanities. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and their ability to tackle the important challenges facing America.